defaultPI 107 – Annual cost of salting per km of network salteddefault. 
defaultThis 
defaultmea
defaultsures the annual cost 
defaultand
default is calculated by using the total annual service provider / client cost for the winter maintenance function figure which includes profit, winter maintenance costs, overheads, charges for the vehicles and central establishment charges.  This figure does not
default include asset rentals, debt charges and other capital charges or management and overhead costs of the service purchaser
default 
default/commissioning organisation (e.g. client unit).  The figure is then divided by the total km of the highway network which is covered by 
defaultthe salting regime.
defaultThe annual cost of salting per km increased significantly between 2007-08 and 2009-10 but subsequently dropped again. The increase coincided with a heavier demand on the service so is understandable as it included increased costs for it
defaultems such as extra salt and the driver costs of extra runs.  The costs then flattened out and decreased reflecting good practice in terms of efficiencies and reduced costs even though the weather was remained severe. 
